<TITLE> Top 'gangster' killed in Fatikchharhi </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Jan 30 (bdnews24.com)--An alleged top crime gang chief was killed in a purported gunfight with the RAB and police in Chittagong's Fatikchharhi Upazila early on Saturday. The deceased was identified as 35-year old Osman Gani, the chief of 'Osman gang'. RAB-7 staff officer ASP Sajjad Hossain told bdnews24.com that they along with police personnel had raided Rangamatia at around 3:45am on a tip off that Osman had been staying there with his associates. The criminals opened fire on the law enforcers, forcing the raiders to fire back, he claimed. At one point of the shootout, Osman was shot and his associates escaped. He was rushed to Fatikchharhi hospital where he was declared him dead on arrival, Hossain said. Two foreign revolvers, one local light gun and three rounds of bullet were recovered from the spot. Osman faced at least 20 cases including two murder charges at different police stations of Chittagong, the RAB official said. b
